Kirinyaga Governor Anne Waiguru has been installed as the patron of a women's group dubbed Daughters of the Mountain.
The colourful ceremony was held Thursday night at her home in Kagio village. 
There was pomp and dance as Ms Waiguru, donned in traditional regalia and beaded necklace, was given a flywhisk as a sign of her leadership position in the group which comprises of young professional women from across Mt Kenya region.



