Another member of the group, Anne Waruguru, said they are also counselling girls from the region to take education seriously and uphold their culture in order to live better lives and be responsible.
In response, Ms Waiguru said she felt honoured to be crowned the patron of the group and promised to steer it to great success.
"I will work with the group for the betterment of all women.Women face a lot of challenges in life and I swore to myself that I will not fight a woman who will be pursuing any political interest or working hard to excell in life," she said.
She told off Deputy President William Ruto's allies who are opposed to the BBI.
She asked residents of Mt Kenya to ignore the DP's allies and vote in favour of BBI when the referrendum is held.
She pleaded with the residents to support BBI as it will ensure the region takes up one of the top national seats.
"The BBI is good for us as our people will be represented in the national government," she added.
Further, Ms Waiguru noted that BBI provides for gender equality and minimum guranteed returns foe coffee and tea farmers.
She also  said BBI will bring peace in the country as power will be shared among all regions.



